"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596087","Women and Equalities","false","2016-10-17","<p>All Government Departments are bound by legal requirements concerning the right to work in the UK and, in addition, the Civil Service Nationality Rules.</p><p> </p><p>Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service as part of wider pre-employment checks, but there is no requirement on departments to retain this information beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p><p> </p><p>More broadly, the Government will be consulting in due course on how we work with business to ensure that workers in this country have the skills that they need to get a job. However, there are no proposals to publish lists of the number or proportion of foreign workers.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","47585","2016-10-17T16:29:43.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596087/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596087/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596087/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2016-10-07","Government Equalities Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, approximately how many (a) British and (b) non-British nationals are employed cleaning the Westminster estate of the Government Equalities Office.","false","Biography information for John Pugh","Southport","John Pugh","47563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596088","Women and Equalities","false","2016-10-17","<p>All Government Departments are bound by legal requirements concerning the right to work in the UK and, in addition, the Civil Service Nationality Rules.</p><p> </p><p>Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service as part of wider pre-employment checks, but there is no requirement on departments to retain this information beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p><p> </p><p>More broadly, the Government will be consulting in due course on how we work with business to ensure that workers in this country have the skills that they need to get a job. However, there are no proposals to publish lists of the number or proportion of foreign workers.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","47563","2016-10-17T16:29:44.017Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596088/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596088/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596088/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2016-10-07","Government Equalities Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what proportion of staff on the payroll of the Government Equalities Office who work in Westminster are (a) British nationals and (b) nationals of another country.","false","Biography information for John Pugh","Southport","John Pugh","47585"
