"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596204","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-17","<p>All Government Departments are bound by legal requirements concerning the right to work in the UK and, in addition, the Civil Service Nationality Rules.</p><p> </p><p>Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service as part of wider pre-employment checks, but there is no requirement on departments to retain this information beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p><p> </p><p>More broadly, the Government will be consulting in due course on how we work with business to ensure that workers in this country have the skills that they need to get a job. But there are no proposals to publish lists of the number or proportion of foreign workers.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-10-17T16:56:07.63Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596204/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596204/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596204/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-07","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what proportion of staff on the payroll of his Department who work in Westminster are (a) British nationals and (b) nationals of another country.","false","Biography information for John Pugh","Southport","John Pugh","47575"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596205","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-12","<p>The newly created Department for International Trade (DIT) has been forged out of the forerunner (non-ministerial) Departments UK Trade and Investment (UKTI) and the Trade Policy Unit responsibilities previously held by the Department for Business Innovation and Skills (BIS). My Rt. Hon Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade also has responsibility for UK Export Finance (the Export Credits Guarantee Department), which has its own budget.</p><p>The estimated annual budgeted operating costs of the department for the next four years are currently being established and will be submitted to parliament later this financial year.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-12T15:29:53.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596205/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596205/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596205/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Department for International Trade: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, if he will publish his Department's budget for the next four years.","false","Biography information for Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","Ochil and South Perthshire","Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","47482"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596206","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-12","<p>The Government’s priorities remain to increase the number of businesses exporting, and the value of UK exports. The manifesto set the target for UK export value to be at £1 trillion in 2020 and to have 100k more exporters in 2020 than in 2010. The scale of these targets demonstrate the ambition this Government has for making the UK an exporting nation again.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-12T15:32:36.467Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596206/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596206/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what targets the Government has set for the growth of UK exports by 2020.","false","Biography information for Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","Ochil and South Perthshire","Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","47483"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596207","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-17","<p>The Prime Minister has been clear, we are not going to provide a running commentary on every twist and turn of these negotiations. We recognise the need for a smooth transition as the UK leaves the EU which minimises disruption to our trading relationships. Ministers and officials in the Department for International Trade are working closely with counterparts across a wide range of markets in order to promote the UK as a great place to do business and with which to trade. We are taking advantage of all the opportunities available to us to ensure that Britain becomes the global leader in free trade once we leave the EU.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-17T11:35:51.637Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596207/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596207/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what discussions he has had with representatives of the 53 countries with which Britain holds free trade agreements (FTAs) through its membership of the EU on the timetable for replacing those agreements with bilateral FTAs.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","47468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596208","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-17","<p>The UK remains committed to supporting an ambitious Transatlantic Trade and Investment deal which cuts regulatory and bureaucratic barriers without lowering standards, removes the remaining tariffs between the EU and US, and opens up opportunities for businesses.</p><p>As hon. Members will have read in a letter from my noble Friend the Minister of State (Lord Price CVO) for Trade Policy on 11 October, the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership reading room will be open from 19 October. This will allow all hon. Members and Peers to view documents that the European Commission and US have agreed can be shared with national parliamentarians on a confidential basis.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-17T11:38:56.44Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596208/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596208/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596208/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 7 June 2016 to Question 38925, what the planned opening date is for a reading room for hon. Members to scrutinise classified documents relating to the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership.","false","Biography information for Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","Ochil and South Perthshire","Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","47444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596209","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-17","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 11 October to the hon. Member for Carmarthen East and Dinefwr (Jonathan Edwards), UIN 46479.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-17T11:37:33.567Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596209/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596209/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596209/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 29 June 2016 to Question 41468, when he plans to lay the draft text of the EU-Canada Comprehensive and Economic Trade Agreement before Parliament.","false","Biography information for Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","Ochil and South Perthshire","Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","47434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596210","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-13","<p>Following her appointment on 13 July 2016 the Prime Minister established the Department for International Trade (DIT). The DIT aggregates UK Trade and Investment (UKTI), UK Export and Finance (UKEF), Trade Policy Units from the Department for Business, Energy &amp; Industrial Strategy (BEIS), as well as some new hires.</p><p>Until such time as a transfer of functions order establishes my Rt hon. Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade as a corporation sole, DIT remains a unified Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) and Department for Business, Energy &amp; Industrial Strategy (BEIS) department for accounting purposes.</p><p>As DIT is currently being formed, details of the staff that the Department employs is being finalised, whilst employee transfers and recruitment are taking place.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","47396","2016-10-13T10:43:40.413Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596210/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596210/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596210/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Department for International Trade: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many foreign workers his Department employs.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","47419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596211","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-13","<p>Following her appointment on 13 July 2016 the Prime Minister established the Department for International Trade (DIT). The DIT aggregates UK Trade and Investment (UKTI), UK Export and Finance (UKEF), Trade Policy Units from the Department for Business, Energy &amp; Industrial Strategy (BEIS), as well as some new hires.</p><p>Until such time as a transfer of functions order establishes my Rt hon. Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade as a corporation sole, DIT remains a unified Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) and Department for Business, Energy &amp; Industrial Strategy (BEIS) department for accounting purposes.</p><p>As DIT is currently being formed, details of the staff that the Department employs is being finalised, whilst employee transfers and recruitment are taking place.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","47419","2016-10-13T10:43:40.35Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596211/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596211/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596211/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Department for International Trade: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, (a) how many and (b) what proportion of the staff employed by his Department are non-UK nationals.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","47396"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596212","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-12","<p>Ministers and senior Government officials have held regular discussions with Japanese investors operating in the UK since the referendum in June. This continued after the Japanese Government published their memorandum on 2 September. My Rt. Hon Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade and my Noble Friend the Minister of State for Trade Policy have met with the Ambassador of Japan to the United Kingdom Mr Koji Tsuruoka. On 4 October my Noble Friend the Minister of State for Trade Policy met Japanese investors to hear their views and my Hon. Friend the Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for International Trade also met Japanese investors while in Japan on 5-6 October.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-12T15:34:32.677Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596212/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596212/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596212/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Foreign Companies: Japan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what discussions he has had with representatives of Japanese businesses operating in the UK on the memorandum presented by the Japanese government to the Prime Minister at the recent G20 summit.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","47347"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596213","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-17","<p>I refer the hon. Member for Southport to the answer I gave to the hon. Member for Birmingham, Selly Oak on 13 October, UIN 47419, 47396.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","47567","2016-10-17T11:28:10.16Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596213/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596213/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596213/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Department for International Trade: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what proportion of staff on the payroll of his Department who work in Westminster are (a) British nationals and (b) nationals of another country.","false","Biography information for John Pugh","Southport","John Pugh","47589"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596214","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-17","<p>I refer the hon. Member for Southport to the answer I gave to the hon. Member for Birmingham, Selly Oak on 13 October, UIN 47419, 47396.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","47589","2016-10-17T11:28:10.237Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596214/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596214/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596214/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Department for International Trade: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, approximately how many (a) British and (b) non-British nationals are employed cleaning the Westminster estate of his Department.","false","Biography information for John Pugh","Southport","John Pugh","47567"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596215","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-17","<p>Information on the Trade in Services Agreement (TiSA) can be found on the European Commission’s dedicated TiSA website. In a bid to encourage transparency, the European Commission has published a large number of documents including its revised TiSA offer from May 2016, the EU proposals for institutional provisions and state-to-state dispute settlement, position papers and factsheets.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-17T11:40:25.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596215/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596215/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596215/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Trade in Services Agreement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, if he will publish the latest proposals on the Trade in Services Agreement.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","46798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596216","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-17","<p>Negotiations of the Trade in Services Agreement (TiSA) are ongoing. A trade sustainability impact assessment is being conducted on the TiSA. The terms of reference of the report include analysis of the impact of the TiSA on climate change. The final inception report can be found on the European Commission’s DG Trade website.</p><p>The Department for International Trade works closely with the Department of Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy and other departments to ensure the TiSA aligns with the UK’s wider policy objectives. Irrespective of what is agreed in TiSA, all signatories to the Paris agreement will have to meet their climate change commitments under that agreement.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-17T16:52:40.71Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596216/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596216/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596216/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Trade in Services Agreement: Climate Change Convention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that the Trade in Services Agreement supports the targets set at the COP21 climate change conference.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","46800"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596217","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-17","<p>The Department for International Trade already has a strong and capable trade policy team which has more than doubled in size since 23 June. Over the coming months we will be developing that team to build the world class negotiating strengths needed to deliver the best outcomes for the UK. They will have the depth and breadth of expertise to handle the full range of sectoral and cross-cutting issues that arise in trade agreements, supported by analysts and lawyers. We will continue to hire the brightest and best talent from within the UK civil service and in time, will look to enhance our team by drawing on expertise from elsewhere.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-17T11:41:47.527Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596217/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596217/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596217/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Department for International Trade: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many trade negotiators he has hired since 23 June 2016; and what the aggregate cost is of their contracts.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","46932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596218","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-17","<p>The information will take time to collate. I will place this in the libraries of the House as soon as the information is available.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-17T16:58:44.133Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596218/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596218/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596218/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Department for International Trade: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many times his Department has used the services of (a) PwC, (b) Deloitte, (c) Ernst and Young, (d) KPMG and (e) other consulting firms since his Department was established; and what (i) work was undertaken and (ii) the cost to the public purse was on each such occasion.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596219","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-17","<p>The UK already has World Trade Organisation (WTO) schedules for goods and services, contained within those of the EU.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-17T15:30:40.677Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596219/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596219/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596219/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what schedules his Department has prepared for World Trade Organisation tariffs on goods and services for the period after the UK has exited the EU.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","47107"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596220","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-17","<p>The newly created Department for International Trade (DIT) has been formed from the previous UK Trade and Investent (UKTI) and from the Trade Policy Unit of the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS). My Rt hon. Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade also has responsibility for UK Export Finance (the Export Credits Guarantee Department), which has its own budget.</p><p>The estimated annual budgeted operating costs of the department for the next four years are currently being established and will be submitted to parliament later this financial year.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-17T16:33:15.117Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596220/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596220/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596220/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Department for International Trade: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what his Department's capital and current budgets are for (a) 2016-17 and (b) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","47108"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596221","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-17","<p>Withdrawing from the EU will give us the opportunity to shape our own international trade and investment opportunities, drive even greater openness with international partners and put Britain firmly at the forefront of global trade and investment.</p><p>We already enjoy excellent trading relationships with Commonwealth partners and we are committed to strengthening these further.</p><p>The UK is co-hosting, with Malta, the inaugural Commonwealth Trade Minister’s meeting in London in March 2017. This will be an excellent opportunity to promote greater trade and investment within the Commonwealth.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-17T16:14:53.217Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596221/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596221/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596221/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Trade Promotion: Commonwealth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what recent assessment he has made of the potential effect of the UK withdrawing from the EU on the promotion of UK trade with other Commonwealth countries.","false","Biography information for Mr William Wragg","Hazel Grove","William Wragg","47043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596222","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-17","<p>My Rt. hon Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade met with the EU Commissioner for Trade, Cecilia Malmström at the European Commission offices in Geneva on September 27.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-17T16:11:50.247Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596222/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596222/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596222/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Department for International Trade: European Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, which EU commissioners he has met since taking office; and when and where such meetings took place.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","47035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596223","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-17","<p>My Rt hon. Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade has been only accompanied by Government officials on all foreign visits.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-17T16:13:17.68Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596223/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596223/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596223/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-07","Department for International Trade: Visits Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 16 September 2016 to Question 45359, whether people not from government departments have accompanied him on official visits abroad.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","46896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596224","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-13","<p>The Department for Exiting the EU now has over 200 staff, and is growing fast. The overall size and scope of the new Department, including staffing and budget, are regularly reviewed. We will ensure we are appropriately staffed to deal with all aspects of the forthcoming negotiation. There are currently 43 (French) speaker slots in UKRep, for which the staff require operational language skills to undertake the post. For the wider Department there are a number of staff with language skills, however these are not currently a requirement of the posts and were not the determining factor in recruitment. We are undertaking work to identify the skills required for the future so this position may change in due course.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2016-10-13T10:12:01.017Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596224/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596224/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596224/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Department for Exiting the European Union: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to his Oral Statement of 5 September 2016, Official Report, columns 38 to 41, how many of his Department's 300 officials were recruited for their ability to speak a second language.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","46992"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596225","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-12","<p>The Government has clearly stated that the UK does not need to be part of the EU to have strong protections for workers' rights. At every step of these negotiations we will work to ensure the best possible outcome for the British people, seizing opportunities to make Britain a country that truly works not just for a privileged few, but for everybody.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2016-10-12T16:30:30.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596225/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596225/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596225/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Insolvency: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what the Government's policy is on maintaining the provisions of European Commission Directive 2008/94/EC on the protection of employees in the event of the insolvency of their employer; and what assessment the Government has made of the effect the UK leaving the EU will have on the operation of the Pension Protection Fund.","false","Biography information for Richard Arkless","Dumfries and Galloway","Richard  Arkless","46991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596226","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-17","<p>My Department, working with officials across government, continues to undertake a wide range of data analyses to inform the UK's position for the upcoming negotiations with our EU partners. We have been clear that we will not provide a running commentary that might undermine our negotiating position.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","46933 ; 47102 ; 47891","2016-10-17T14:08:35.91Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596226/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596226/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596226/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what assessment his Department has made of the value of UK access to the single market.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","47051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596227","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-17","<p>My Department, working with officials across government, continues to undertake a wide range of data analyses to inform the UK's position for the upcoming negotiations with our EU partners. We have been clear that we will not provide a running commentary that might undermine our negotiating position.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","46933 ; 47051 ; 47891","2016-10-17T14:08:35.963Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596227/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596227/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596227/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what estimate he has made of the proportion of exports from the UK by volume and value which would be covered by rules of origin by sector in (a) 2016-17 and (b) each of the next three financial years.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","47102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596228","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-12","<p>The Prime Minister has been clear we will not give a running commentary on Brexit negotiations. We will ensure that we engage closely with all relevant interlocutors.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2016-10-12T16:27:42.007Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596228/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596228/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596228/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Department for Exiting the European Union: European Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, which EU Commissioners he has met with since taking office; and when and where such meetings took place.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","47331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596229","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-17","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union has used the services of a number of consulting firms to help with departmental set-up and planning. The cost to the public purse on each occasion was either nil or nominal fee (£1). Two individuals are on secondment from consultancy firms, incurring a cost to the department equivalent to median civil service salary levels.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-10-17T13:55:09.917Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596229/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596229/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596229/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Department for Exiting the European Union: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many times his Department has used the services of (a) PwC, (b) Deloitte, (c) Ernst and Young, (d) KPMG and (e) other consulting firms since his Department was established; and what (i) work was undertaken and (ii) the cost to the public purse was on each such occasion.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596230","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-17","<p>The Prime Minister has been clear that during negotiations she wants to protect the status of EU nationals already living here, and the only circumstances in which that would not be possible is if British citizens’ rights in European member states were not also protected.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-10-17T16:18:07.363Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596230/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596230/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596230/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, if he will take steps to let current EU staff and students know they are welcome to stay beyond the UK exit from the EU.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","47192"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596231","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-17","<p>The Government has been clear that we will make a success of Brexit, including for our world class universities. The Government is committed to ensuring that the UK remains a world leader in international research and innovation collaboration and that is why the Government has been consulting, and will continue to consult, with a broad range of stakeholders in this sector.</p><p>We are not going to provide a running commentary on every twist and turn of the negotiations, but we will work hard to get the best deal for Britain, its universities, and the wider research sector.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2016-10-17T16:08:27.173Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596231/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596231/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596231/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Universities: International Cooperation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, if he will take steps to make international collaboration between UK and EU universities a key part of the negotiations on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","47193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596232","Department for Education","false","2016-10-24","<p>University researchers can continue to bid for competitive EU research funding while we remain a member of the EU. We will work with the Commission to ensure payment when funds are awarded. HM Treasury will underwrite the payment of such awards, even when specific projects continue beyond the UK’s departure from the EU. Further details about Government safeguarding funding can be found in the statement Jo Johnson made on 13 August: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/safeguarding-funding-for-research-and-innovation" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/safeguarding-funding-for-research-and-innovation</a></p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-10-24T16:05:05.5Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596232/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596232/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596232/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-07","Universities: EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will take steps to guarantee to match any EU funding lost to universities and colleges.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","47196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596233","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-17","<p>We are working towards securing the best possible deal for the whole United Kingdom. It will be for Parliament to determine which legislation should or should not be repealed after the passage of the Great Repeal Act. The Bill will help to provide certainty to businesses, consumers, workers and voluntary organisations by preserving all existing EU law.</p><p>DExEU will be working closely with every Government department to ensure that the full range of opportunities are taken and risks mitigated across every area of Government policy.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-10-17T16:09:23.837Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596233/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596233/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596233/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether his Department has made an estimate of the total cost to the public purse of repealing EU legislation; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","47200"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596234","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-17","<p>The UK has continued to participate in the European Foundation for the Improvement of Living and Working Conditions (Eurofound) since the EU referendum vote. Future engagement between the UK and Eurofound will be considered as part of the broader EU exit negotiations.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-10-17T15:40:38.937Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596234/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596234/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596234/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-07","European Foundation for the Improvement of Living and Working Conditions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the Government plans to continue to participate in the European Foundation for the Improvement of Living and Working Conditions after the UK leaves the UK.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596235","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-10-13","<p>While the UK remains a member of the EU we are required to fully participate in the European Environment Agency (EEA) as an EEA member country.</p><p>As we start the process of leaving the EU, we will aim to deliver a stable and clear legislative framework for the environment, including maintaining standards that underpin trade and deliver on our international commitments. It is within this framework that we will plan our future participation in the EEA.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-10-13T12:44:03.973Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596235/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596235/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596235/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-10-07","European Environment Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether the Government plans to continue to participate in the European Environment Agency after the UK leaves the UK.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596236","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-17","<p>The Government is considering carefully all the potential implications arising from the UK’s exit from the EU, including the implications for our future relationship with agencies such as the European Railways Agency and the European Maritime Safety Agency. Until we leave, EU law still applies, and current arrangements will continue.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","47164","2016-10-17T13:35:25.417Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596236/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596236/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596236/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-07","European Railway Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the Government plans to continue to participate in the European Railways Agency after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596237","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-20","<p>There is no immediate effect on our participation in the European Institute of Innovation and Technology (EIT) while we remain a member of the EU. Post-exit participation in EIT will be a matter for the forthcoming negotiations. We will work through the implications for future years as part of the wider negotiations.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-10-20T13:42:46.597Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596237/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596237/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596237/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-07","European Institute of Innovation and Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the Government plans to continue to participate in the European Institute of Innovation and Technology after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47166"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596238","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-12","<p>The Government is considering options for our future relationship with the EU and European Defence Agency. No final decisions have been taken.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-10-12T15:29:31.433Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596238/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596238/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596238/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-07","European Defence Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the Government plans to continue to participate in the European Defence Agency after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47160"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596239","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-17","<p>The UK will continue to participate in the European Training Foundation until we leave the EU. Future participation after we leave the EU is a matter for the forthcoming negotiations.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-10-17T16:45:57.95Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596239/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596239/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596239/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-07","European Training Foundation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the Government plans to continue to participate in the European Training Foundation after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47167"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596240","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-17","<p>The United Kingdom will continue to participate in the European Agency for Safety and Health at Work while we remain a member of the European Union (EU). Decisions on any future participation after we leave the EU will be dependent on the outcome of the exit negotiations.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-10-17T10:34:07.903Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596240/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596240/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596240/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-07","European Agency for Safety and Health at Work","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether the Government plans to continue to participate in the European Agency for Safety and Health at Work after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596241","Department of Health","false","2016-10-17","<p>The United Kingdom currently participates actively in the work of the European Monitoring Centre for Drugs and Drug Addiction (EMCDDA). Continued participation after the UK leaves the European Union would be a matter for negotiation. The Founding Regulation of the EMCDDA which was recast in 2006 makes provision for the participation of third countries.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-10-17T15:27:10.86Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596241/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596241/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596241/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-07","European Monitoring Centre for Drugs and Drug Addiction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether the Government plans to continue to participate in the European Monitoring Centre for Drugs and Drug Addiction after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47168"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596242","Home Office","false","2016-10-13","<p>The European Border and Coast Guard was launched on 6 October, building on and replacing Frontex. The new Agency builds on provisions of the Schengen agreement in which the UK does not participate. The UK is not therefore bound by the new regulation although we are supportive of steps to increase the security of the external Schengen border and currently participate in Frontex operations on a voluntary basis, agreed by the Management Board.</p><p>Our future cooperation with the European Border and Coast Guard Agency will be considered as part of wider negotiations for the UK’s exit from the EU. The Prime Minister has made clear that the Government will not be giving a running commentary on negotiations.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-10-13T14:05:46.197Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596242/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596242/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596242/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-07","Frontex","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether the Government plans continued participation in Frontex after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596243","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-17","<p>The European Intellectual Property Office is a decentralised Agency of the European Union. After leaving the EU, UK businesses will continue to be able to apply to that organisation for EU Trade Marks and Registered Community Designs covering the member states of the EU.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-10-17T16:39:12.647Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596243/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596243/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596243/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-07","European Union Intellectual Property Office","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the Government plans continued participation in the European Intellectual Property Office after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47169"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596244","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-12","<p>The Secretary of State welcomes the report HL44 by the Constitution Committee, issued on 12 September, and will respond in due course in the usual way.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2016-10-12T16:07:47.91Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596244/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596244/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596244/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what assessment he has made of the implications for his Department's policies of the recommendations in the fourth report of the House of Lords Committee on the Constitution Session 2016-17, HL44.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596245","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-14","<p>As we leave the EU, our country is embarking on an important negotiation. As my right hon. Friend the Prime Minister has already said, we are not going to provide a running commentary on every twist and turn of the negotiation.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-10-14T10:03:48.803Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596245/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596245/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596245/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-07","European GNSS Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the Government plans to continue to participate in the European GNSS Agency after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596246","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-20","<p>The UK will continue to participate in the European Centre for the Development of Vocational Training until we leave the EU. Future participation after we leave the EU is a matter for the forthcoming negotiations.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-10-20T13:42:03.09Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596246/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596246/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596246/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-07","European Centre for the Development of Vocational Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the Government plans continued participation in the European Centre for the Development of Vocational Training after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47171"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596247","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-17","<p>The Government is considering carefully all the potential implications arising from the UK’s exit from the EU, including the implications for our future relationship with agencies such as the European Railways Agency and the European Maritime Safety Agency. Until we leave, EU law still applies, and current arrangements will continue.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","47158","2016-10-17T13:35:25.497Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596247/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596247/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596247/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-07","European Maritime Safety Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the Government plans to continue to participate in the European Maritime Safety Agency after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596248","Department for Education","false","2016-10-17","<p>The negotiations we are about to undertake will include our relationship with a wide range of EU organisations and institutions, the European Institute for Gender Equality being one of them. How we take these various relationships forward will be a matter for discussion with the EU institutions and our European partners.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-10-17T16:21:35.67Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596248/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596248/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596248/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-07","European Institute for Gender Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether the Government plans to continue to participate in the European Institute for Gender Equality after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47159"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596249","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-17","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given on 17th October 2016 to the Question 47173.</p><p>Nothing has yet been decided on whether the UK will continue participation in the European Centre for Disease Control after leaving the European Union. Officials in both the Department of Health and the Department for Exiting the European Union are considering the position and options available to us with the aim of achieving the best outcome for the UK health system and for the UK as a whole.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-10-17T16:28:55.973Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596249/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596249/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596249/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether the Government plans to continue to participate in the European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47165"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596250","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-17","<p>My Department, working with officials across government, continues to undertake a wide range of data analyses to inform the UK's position for the upcoming negotiations with our EU partners. We have been clear that we will not provide a running commentary that might undermine our negotiating position.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","47051 ; 47102 ; 47891","2016-10-17T14:08:35.837Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596250/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596250/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596250/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","EU External Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what estimate he has made of the (a) value and (b) volume of imports by sector, from non-EU countries that were exported to countries in the EU as (i) components and (ii) free standing items in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","46933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596251","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-17","<p>There are currently no plans to use citizens' juries to define the UK's future relationship with the EU.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-10-17T14:17:11.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596251/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596251/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","UK Relations with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what his policy is on the use of citizens' juries to define the UK's future relationship with the EU.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","46839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596252","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-17","<p>All Government Departments are bound by legal requirements concerning the right to work in the UK and, in addition, the Civil Service Nationality Rules.</p><p>Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service as part of wider pre-employment checks, but there is no requirement on departments to retain this information beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p><p>More broadly, the Government will be consulting in due course on how we work with business to ensure that workers in this country have the skills that they need to get a job. But there are no proposals to publish lists of the number or proportion of foreign workers.</p><p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","47583","2016-10-17T14:58:44.187Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596252/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596252/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596252/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Department for Exiting the European Union: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, approximately how many (a) British and (b) non-British nationals are employed cleaning the Westminster estate of his Department.","false","Biography information for John Pugh","Southport","John Pugh","47561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596253","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-17","<p>The Prime Minister has been clear we will not give a running commentary on Brexit negotiations. We will ensure that we engage closely with all relevant interlocutors.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-10-17T14:18:45.637Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596253/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596253/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596253/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Michel Barnier","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what discussions he has had with Michel Barnier and on how many occasions about the UK's exit from the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596254","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-12","<p>The European Union (EU) Staff employed at Northwood within the EU Operational Headquarters (OHQ) and the NATO Maritime Commander (MARCOM)'s Headquarters provide vital support to Operation ATALANTA (a Counter-Piracy mission off the Horn of Africa) and broader NATO Maritime Operations.</p><p>The requirement for the OHQ, its location, and its EU Staff depend on a continuing mandate (expected to be extended until December 2018) and decisions of the EU; and the UK supports continued NATO - EU cooperation including that through MARCOM.</p><p>There are are no current plans to relocate the OHQ or EU staff from Northwood.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","47457","2016-10-12T15:31:29.09Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596254/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596254/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596254/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-07","Military Bases: Northwood","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he plans that the Multi National Headquarters for the command of EU military operations will remain at Northwood.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","47458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596255","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-17","<p>All Government Departments are bound by legal requirements concerning the right to work in the UK and, in addition, the Civil Service Nationality Rules.</p><p>Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service as part of wider pre-employment checks, but there is no requirement on departments to retain this information beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p><p>More broadly, the Government will be consulting in due course on how we work with business to ensure that workers in this country have the skills that they need to get a job. But there are no proposals to publish lists of the number or proportion of foreign workers.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-10-17T14:13:14.89Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596255/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596255/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596255/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Department for Exiting the European Union: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, (a) how many and (b) what proportion of staff employed by his Department are non-UK nationals.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","47414"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596256","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-12","<p>DExEU officials, supported by officials across Government, are engaging with business to identify the key factors that will affect our negotiations with the EU. We have a formal strategy and are engaging with companies big and small in every sector of the economy and are drawing on local and regional networks and key organisations in the voluntary sector.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","47496","2016-10-12T16:21:19.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596256/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596256/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596256/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many meetings his Department has had with representatives of each sector of the economy on exiting the EU since he took office.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","47495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596257","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-12","<p>DExEU officials, supported by officials across Government, are engaging with business to identify the key factors that will affect our negotiations with the EU. We have a formal strategy and are engaging with companies big and small in every sector of the economy and are drawing on local and regional networks and key organisations in the voluntary sector.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","47495","2016-10-12T16:21:19.257Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596257/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596257/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596257/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether he plans to implement a formal process for engaging with sectors of the economy affected by the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","47496"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596258","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-12","<p>The European Union (EU) Staff employed at Northwood within the EU Operational Headquarters (OHQ) and the NATO Maritime Commander (MARCOM)'s Headquarters provide vital support to Operation ATALANTA (a Counter-Piracy mission off the Horn of Africa) and broader NATO Maritime Operations.</p><p>The requirement for the OHQ, its location, and its EU Staff depend on a continuing mandate (expected to be extended until December 2018) and decisions of the EU; and the UK supports continued NATO - EU cooperation including that through MARCOM.</p><p>There are are no current plans to relocate the OHQ or EU staff from Northwood.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","47458","2016-10-12T15:31:29.167Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596258/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596258/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-07","Military Bases: Northwood","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he plans to require that EU staff employed at Northwood relocate to another country after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","47457"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596259","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-13","<p>At every step of these negotiations we will work to ensure the best possible outcome for the British people, including those living in other EU countries or who own property in the EU. It is already the case that all Member States are bound by Article 1 of Protocol 1 to the European Convention on Human Rights which obliges them to respect property rights.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","47486","2016-10-13T10:08:46.047Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596259/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596259/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596259/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Property: EU Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what steps the Government plans to take to protect the property ownership rights of UK citizens who own property in the EU after the UK has left the EU who (a) use the property primarily to rent out to others for holidays, (b) are the sole users, for holiday purposes and (c) are the sole users, and live there permanently.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","47485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596260","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-13","<p>At every step of these negotiations we will work to ensure the best possible outcome for the British people, including those living in other EU countries or who own property in the EU. It is already the case that all Member States are bound by Article 1 of Protocol 1 to the European Convention on Human Rights which obliges them to respect property rights.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","47485","2016-10-13T10:08:46.093Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596260/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596260/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596260/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","British Nationals Abroad: EU Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what steps the Government is taking to enable UK citizens living in other EU countries to remain there if they (a) have retired, (b) are working in those countries with habitual residence status and (c) are working in those countries part of the time but without habitual residence status.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","47486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596261","Department for Education","false","2016-10-18","<p>Future arrangements for migration, student funding and UK students studying abroad will need to be considered as part of wider discussions about the UK’s relationship with the EU.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-10-18T16:07:53.427Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596261/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596261/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596261/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-07","Foreign Students: EU Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans she has to ensure that UK students will retain the ability and funding to study at universities elsewhere in the EU after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","47480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596262","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-12","<p>Ministers and officials from across the Government are working closely with Japanese companies operating in the UK to reinforce the continued importance of a close business relationship between our countries. The Department for Exiting the EU will continue to support this work.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-10-12T16:10:37.433Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596262/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596262/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596262/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Foreign Companies: Japan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether he has had discussions with representatives of Japanese businesses operating in the UK pursuant to the memorandum presented by the Japanese government to the Prime Minister at the recent G20 Summit.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","47489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596263","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-12","<p>The Government is assessing the legal and policy implications of the public’s vote to leave the EU including the UK’s membership of EURATOM.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-10-12T16:05:19.367Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596263/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596263/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596263/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-07","EURATOM","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what his policy is on the UK's status as a signatory to the Euratom Treaty after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","47517"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596264","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-17","<p>All Government Departments are bound by legal requirements concerning the right to work in the UK and, in addition, the Civil Service Nationality Rules.</p><p>Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service as part of wider pre-employment checks, but there is no requirement on departments to retain this information beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p><p>More broadly, the Government will be consulting in due course on how we work with business to ensure that workers in this country have the skills that they need to get a job. But there are no proposals to publish lists of the number or proportion of foreign workers.</p><p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","47561","2016-10-17T14:58:44.253Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596264/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596264/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596264/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-07","Department for Exiting the European Union: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what proportion of staff on the payroll of his Department who work in Westminster are (a) British nationals and (b) nationals of another country.","false","Biography information for John Pugh","Southport","John Pugh","47583"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592861","Department of Health","false","2016-10-13","<p>Occasionally, the Human Fertilisation and Embryology Authority (HFEA) engages with the Science Media Centre to deliver press briefings. When it does so, the HFEA works with the Centre to ensure that the relevant science is carefully explained.</p><p> </p><p>The terms of reference of the Scientific and Clinical Advances Advisory Committee are set out in Annex A of the HFEA’s Standing Orders, a copy is attached. The purpose of the Committee is to advise the HFEA on scientific and clinical developments (including research) in assisted conception, embryo research and related areas. The Committee’s functions are to:</p><p> </p><p>- make recommendations to the Authority on the safety and efficacy of scientific and clinical developments (including research) in assisted conception, embryo research and related areas;</p><p>- make recommendations to the Authority on patient information relating to those scientific and clinical developments;</p><p>- advise the Authority on significant implications for licensing and regulation arising out of such developments, and;</p><p>- where required, work with the Authority members to consider the social, ethical and legal implications arising out of such developments.</p><p> </p><p>Many members of the Committee are experts in their own right and may comment on published research in their own capacity.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-10-13T11:05:07.427Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592861/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592861/answer","20161006 - HL1987 HFEA_Standing_orders attachment.pdf","20161006 - HL1987 HFEA_Standing_orders attachment.pdf","HFEA Standing orders","HFEA Standing orders","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592861/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-03","In Vitro Fertilisation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the recent article in the journal Science <i>"Motherless babies!"</i><i>How to create a tabloid science headline in five easy steps</i>, what consideration the Human Fertilisation and Embryology Authority (HFEA) has given to the role of the Science Media Centre in generating claims about assisted reproductive technologies; and what role members of the HFEA’s Scientific and Clinical Advances Advisory Group play in trying to prevent sensationalist or alarmist headlines.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL1987"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592862","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-10-11","<p>We are aware that the four men in question remain in detention. Officials from our Embassy in Khartoum were present in court to observe the most recent hearing on 26 September, and are in close contact with the lawyers representing the defendants. We regularly raise our concerns over this case with the government of Sudan, most recently during the visit of the UK Special Representative for Sudan and South Sudan to Khartoum in September. We will continue to monitor this case closely.</p><p>More widely, freedom of religion or belief remains a consistent theme in our ongoing human rights dialogue with the government of Sudan. We consistently call on them to ensure all legislation is consistent with the commitment to their citizens in the Interim Constitution of 2005, within which religious freedom is enshrined.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","HL1989","2016-10-11T15:58:16.58Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592862/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592862/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592862/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-10-03","Sudan: Religious Freedom","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with the government of Sudan about the arrest and continuing detention of Reverend Hasan Kodi Taour, Reverend Kuwa Shamal Kori, Abdelmonim Abdelmawla and Petr Jasek.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL1988"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592863","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-10-11","<p>We are aware that the four men in question remain in detention. Officials from our Embassy in Khartoum were present in court to observe the most recent hearing on 26 September, and are in close contact with the lawyers representing the defendants. We regularly raise our concerns over this case with the government of Sudan, most recently during the visit of the UK Special Representative for Sudan and South Sudan to Khartoum in September. We will continue to monitor this case closely.</p><p>More widely, freedom of religion or belief remains a consistent theme in our ongoing human rights dialogue with the government of Sudan. We consistently call on them to ensure all legislation is consistent with the commitment to their citizens in the Interim Constitution of 2005, within which religious freedom is enshrined.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","HL1988","2016-10-11T15:58:16.66Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592863/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592863/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592863/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-10-03","Sudan: Religious Freedom","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Anelay of St Johns on 11 May (HL8212), what steps they are taking to ensure that the human rights of Christian pastors in Sudan are protected, in the light of the ongoing detention of Reverend Hasan Kodi Taour.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL1989"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592864","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-10-11","<p>We are concerned by the allegations of the use of chemical weapons in Sudan and we are aware that the Organisation for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons (OPCW) is looking into these. The use of chemical weapons under any circumstances is contrary to international law and we wholly condemned it. We were also concerned to read the other allegations made in the Amnesty International report, which highlight the need for access to conflict-affected areas. We see ensuring access for the UN/AU Peacekeeping Mission throughout Darfur as the most important next step and have raised this in the context of the report with the Sudanese in London, Khartoum and New York.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-10-11T15:58:46.587Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592864/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592864/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592864/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-10-03","Darfur: Chemical Weapons","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the Amnesty International report on the use of chemical weapons in Darfur; whether they intend to ask the UN Human Rights Council in Geneva to open an investigation; and what representations they have made, or plan to make, to the Sudanese Ambassador to London in the light of that report.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL1990"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592865","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-10-11","<p>Our primary focus, in both our political engagement and the work of the Department for International Development, is to support the peaceful development of the country allowing ordinary Sudanese people to have a voice in their future. The first step in this process would be a cessation of hostilities and unrestricted humanitarian access to all areas of the country, including Darfur and the Two Areas of Blue Nile and South Kordofan. We consider all the information at our disposal, including the reports referred to, when assessing the situation on the ground and regularly raise our concerns about violations of human rights and international humanitarian law directly with the government of Sudan, and in international fora where appropriate. We remain a firm supporter of the International Criminal Court and encourage all States to act on its indictments.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-10-11T15:59:22.967Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592865/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592865/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592865/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-10-03","Sudan: Human Rights","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, when considering trade, diplomatic, political and other bilateral links with the Republic of Sudan, what weight they attach to (1) the Amnesty International report on the use of chemical weapons in Darfur; (2) the Médecins Sans Frontières 2000 report <i>Living Under Aerial Bombardment</i>; (3) the Human Rights Watch 2015 report concerning the use of cluster bombs; (4) reports in 2016 of aerial bombardment in Blue Nile and South Kordofan; and (5) the outstanding warrants for the arrest of Sudanese leaders on genocide charges.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL1991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592866","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-10-17","<p>The British Government Office in Raleigh will be run by the member of staff hired locally in the US. Costs are expected to be low and limited to salary, office space rental and discretionary budget for travel and representational activities.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-10-17T14:25:53.813Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592866/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592866/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592866/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-10-03","Trade Promotion: USA","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the budget of the UK Trade Office in Raleigh, North Carolina for (1) 2016–17, and (2) 2017–18.","false","Biography information for Baroness Barker",,"Baroness Barker","HL1992"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592867","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-10-17","<p>The new UK Government Office in Raleigh, North Carolina will promote a broad range of British prosperity interests, including trade and investment and engagement with industry, research and development and higher education institutions. Performance objectives will be agreed with a broad range of HMG stakeholders, including the Department for International Trade, the UK Science and Innovation Network and policy teams in the British Embassy in Washington DC. The Office will be managed and supported by Her Majesty's Consul General in Atlanta.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-10-17T14:26:34.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592867/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592867/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592867/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-10-03","Trade Promotion: USA","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what performance targets they have set for the UK Trade Office in Raleigh, North Carolina for (1) 2016–17, and (2) 2017–18.","false","Biography information for Baroness Barker",,"Baroness Barker","HL1993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592868","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-10-17","The British Government Office in Raleigh, North Carolina will contribute to inward investment objectives in support of the Department for International Trade’s targets for the South East United States. These targets are set by sector. North Carolina has one of the fastest growing economies in the United States. Our office there will allow us to explore opportunities for collaboration with the many institutions and businesses located in Raleigh’s Research Triangle Park.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-10-17T15:26:16.993Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592868/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592868/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592868/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-10-03","Trade Promotion: USA","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much inward investment the UK Trade Office in Raleigh, North Carolina is expected to generate in (1) 2017–18, and (2) 2018–19.","false","Biography information for Baroness Barker",,"Baroness Barker","HL1994"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592869","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-17","<p>Supported accommodation plays a vital role in the lives of many vulnerable people. That is why on 15 September 2016 we announced, via a Written Ministerial Statement, that we would be deferring the application of Local Housing Allowance Rates in the social sector for supported housing until 2019/20, at which point we will bring in a new funding model which will ensure that the sector continues to be funded at current levels, taking into account the effect of Government policy on social sector rents.</p>",,"Lord Freud",,"2016-10-17T11:14:55.87Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592869/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592869/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592869/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-03","Supported Housing: Local Housing Allowance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the number of supported housing properties likely to be affected by the proposed reduction in housing benefit, and what is their estimate of the range of weekly costs to tenants of such properties.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL1995"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592870","Department for Education","false","2016-10-17","<p>I refer Lord Beecham to my Written Answer on 13 September to HL1466. The Prime Minister has been clear that tackling poverty and disadvantage, and delivering real social reform, will be a priority for this Government. We will consider future policy on children’s centres as part of this. We will provide further detail in due course and will make clear how stakeholders and members of the public can contribute.</p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2016-10-17T16:56:30.393Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592870/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592870/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592870/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-03","Children's Centres","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Nash on 1 August (HL1311), whether they intend to publish the response to the consultation on Sure Start; and if not, why not.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL1996"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592871","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-10-20","<p>The evaluation, published on 17 October<em>, </em>comprises several different strands including longitudinal case studies in twenty local authorities, in-depth longitudinal research with families, a face-to-face survey of over 800 families, an impact study using national administrative datasets, the development of a cost savings calculator for local authorities, and a local monitoring system for all local authorities to record family problems. The total value of these strands amount to £1.16 Million (0.2 per cent of the total programme budget).</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2016-10-20T10:48:14.587Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592871/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592871/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592871/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-10-03","Families: Disadvantaged","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth on 19 September (HL1467), how much they will pay Ecorys for the production of their report evaluating the Troubled Families Programme; and whether that fee will be reduced in the light of the reported problems with methodology and the consequent delay in the completion and publication of that report.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL1997"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592872","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-10-11","<p>We have made no enquiries of, or representations to, the Syrian regime on this matter. The UK Government has no contact with the Asad regime due to the atrocities it has committed against the Syrian people.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-10-11T16:01:30.33Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592872/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592872/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592872/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-10-03","Zaina Erhaim","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they have made enquiries of, or representations to, the government of Syria in relation to its claim that the passport of Zaina Erhaim produced at Heathrow on her arrival in the UK had been stolen.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL1998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592873","Department for Education","false","2016-10-17","<p>In July, the Secretary of State committed to introduce national funding formulae for schools and high needs from financial year 2018-19. We are considering the options carefully, taking into account the need to give schools and local authorities stability, and the importance of getting these historic reforms right. We will set out detailed proposals later in the autumn, and make decisions early next year, for the new system to be in place from April 2018.</p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2016-10-17T16:57:17.377Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592873/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592873/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592873/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-03","Schools: Finance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what progress they have made in developing a new formula for school funding; and when the new formula will be applied.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL1999"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592874","Home Office","false","2016-10-11","<p>The ethnicity categories used for data collections are assessed as part of the Home Office’s process of agreeing the Annual Data Requirement (ADR). This is the list of mandatory data collections required from the police.</p><p>This process includes consultation with a range of stakeholders on the requirements for each data collection, together with consideration of the burdens involved in the collection (e.g. IT costs of implementation for police forces), and the likely quality of the data.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2016-10-11T16:25:55.533Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592874/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592874/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592874/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-03","Police: Statistics","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what consideration they have given to amending the Annual Data Requirement to replace the 16+1 ethnicity code based on the 2001 census with the 2011 census ethnicity category 18+1, to include Gypsies and Irish Travellers.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL2000"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592875","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-13","<p>It is not possible to provide the names of HS2 Ltd’s Conflict of Interest Panel Members, nor details of specific cases which have been heard as we do not consider doing so would be consistent with the Data Protection Act 1998 (DPA). Unfair disclosure of personal data is a breach of the First Data Protection Principles under the DPA.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-10-13T12:58:36.82Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592875/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592875/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592875/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-03","High Speed Two","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon on 19 September (HL1473), who are the members of HS2 Ltd.’s Conflict of Interest Panel; which cases of potential conflict of interest they have considered in the last year; what was their decision in each case; and whether they intend to publish this information every six months in the future.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL2001"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592876","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-13","<p>The next East Midlands franchise is due to start in July 2018 and we are currently undertaking a process of information gathering to develop the high-level view of the franchise specification. We are due to begin a public consultation later this year to inform the specification. Until the views submitted through the public consultation are understood and further analysis is conducted on the options for the franchise, a firm decision cannot be taken at this stage. I would encourage the noble Lord to make his views known through the formal public consultation process when it opens.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-10-13T13:03:16.433Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592876/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592876/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592876/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-03","Luton Airport: Railways","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether, in the light of the planned expansion of Luton Airport from 10 million to 18 million passengers a year, they intend to include in the specification for the new Midland Main Line longer-distance passenger service a requirement that four trains per hour per direction should call at Luton Parkway in order to increase the percentage of air passengers arriving by rail.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL2002"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592877","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-10-12","<p>The new Governance Code for Sport in the UK will be published shortly. It will build on the existing governance requirements of UK Sport and Sport England and set out new governance standards that will be expected of all sports bodies seeking public funding. It will be for UK Sport and/or Sport England to determine compliance.</p><p><br></p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2016-10-12T16:06:43.917Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592877/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592877/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592877/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-10-03","Football Association","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Ashton of Hyde on 12 September (HL1480), how they will establish whether the Football Association is adhering to the new Code of Governance.","false","Biography information for Lord Birt",,"Lord Birt","HL2003"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592878","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-13","<p>The Government wants to deliver better journeys for drivers. Roadworks are essential, but that doesn’t mean they should be in place any longer than is absolutely necessary. We continue to keep the implementation and operation of the relevant legislation and statutory guidance under constant review, and are taking opportunities to streamline, simplify and de-regulate what has become a complex legislative framework where possible.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, we are modernising and updating secondary legislation and statutory guidance where this is necessary and where it will lead to improvements in the way that road and street works are managed. Recent examples include consultations earlier this year on updated statutory guidance relating to inspections and modernised regulations relating to the qualifications regime. In 2015, we updated regulations and guidance on permit schemes that are now in place in over 55% of local authority areas and which are resulting in more effective management of street works and reductions in the duration of works.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-10-13T12:56:00.787Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592878/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592878/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592878/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-03","Road Works","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether, in the light of the impact of highway works and their management by utilities and local authorities on traffic congestion and delays to road traffic, they have any plans to review the operation of the New Roads and Street Works Act 1991 or the Traffic Management Act 2004.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL2004"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592879","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-13","<p>The Government has an ambitious strategy for tackling congestion in our cities and towns and improving performance on our roads. This strategy includes providing significant investment in both our strategic and local road networks, as well as encouraging more sustainable transport including buses, light rail and walking and cycling. We are providing £15.2 billion between 2015 and 2021 to invest in our strategic road network. This is the biggest upgrade to our motorways and ‘A’ roads for a generation, and it is adding capacity and tackling congestion.</p><p> </p><p>The Road Investment Strategy is providing a transformational level of investment in the strategic road network (SRN), with over 400 extra lane miles of Smart Motorways, including a ‘smart spine’ linking London, Birmingham and the North West and schemes to improve critical freight routes, such as the £1.5 billion A14 scheme in Cambridgeshire and the M6 in Cheshire.</p><p> </p><p>The drive to improve safety and reduce congestion underpins the vast majority of our schemes. Several schemes, however, are specifically focused on alleviating these problems – the two of which often go hand in hand. On the M25, upgrades to Junction 10 will create a free-flowing interchange with the A3, improving an area which has a high casualty rate. In the North, planning work will start for upgrades to two of the region’s most important interchanges: the M62/M1 Lofthouse interchange and the M60/M62/M66 Simister Island junction.</p><p> </p><p>On local roads we have the £12 billion Local Growth Fund to 2021 which has enabled local authorities through the Local Enterprise Partnerships to identify and secure funding for projects to enable among other things, local road improvements and sustainable local transport projects. This is on top of over £6 billion through to 2021 to councils in England to help maintain their local roads and repair potholes.</p><p> </p><p>This investment is set against the backdrop of a regulatory framework that is intended to provide better conditions for all road users through coordination and proactive management of the road network. The Traffic Management Act 2004 specifically places a network management duty on each local traffic authority in England to manage its road network to secure the expeditious movement of traffic on its own network and to facilitate the same on the network of other authorities. This can be achieved through traditional traffic management methods including effective enforcement of parking and management of street works but increasingly also through the deployment of technology. To support this the Department for Transport is currently inviting local authorities to bid for a share of £2m to fund demonstrator projects to test these new technologies.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-10-13T12:57:46.427Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592879/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592879/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592879/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-03","Road Traffic Control","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have to tackle traffic congestion.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL2005"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592880","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-13","<p>Managing traffic congestion on the local road network, over which most buses operate, is the responsibility of local highway authorities.</p><p> </p><p>The Government recognises that traffic congestion impacts on the punctuality and reliability of bus services and continues to work collaboratively with the bus industry, local authorities and other stakeholders to promote effective strategies to tackle this issue, such as operator/authority partnership working and the introduction of bus priority measures.</p><p> </p><p>The average traffic speed on locally managed ‘A’ roads in England is estimated to have decreased by 3.3% since 2014, when the Department started measuring speeds over the full 24 hours of the day.</p><p> </p><p>Bus punctuality data is collected and managed by local authorities, and published by the Department for Transport in online statistical tables.</p><p>The Department publishes two measures of bus punctuality for frequent and non-frequent bus services. A frequent service is one that has six or more buses per hour.</p><p> </p><p>For frequent services, statistics by local authority are available in table BUS0903. This measure represents the excess waiting time arising from irregular gaps between services.</p><p> </p><p>The proportion of non-frequent bus services in England running on-time is published in table BUS0902. Both tables are attached to this response.</p><p> </p><p>The latest statistics show that in 2014/15, 83% of non-frequent services ran on-time compared with 80% in 2009/10. ‘On-time’ is defined as one between 1 minute early and 5 minutes 59 seconds late.</p><p> </p><p>Ministers and officials have discussed the issue of congestion with Greener Journeys and representatives of the bus industry and local authorities, including at an event in the House of Commons on 14 September.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-10-13T13:24:32.817Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592880/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592880/answer","HL2006 - Bus0902.xls ; HL2006 - Bus0903.xlsx","HL2006 - Bus0902.xls ; HL2006 - Bus0903.xlsx","Bus Statistics - Average excess waiting time ; Bus Statistics - Running on time","Bus Statistics - Average excess waiting time ; Bus Statistics - Running on time","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592880/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-03","Bus Services","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the economic impact on the bus industry of increased traffic congestion, in particular in respect of (1) bus speeds, (2) the deployment of additional vehicles to maintain service intervals, and (3) the attractiveness of the bus as a means of travel; and whether they have discussed this subject with the bus industry and local highway authorities.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL2006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592881","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-13","<p>The Government has introduced several measures to encourage the uptake of environmentally friendly buses.</p><p> </p><p>The Low Emission Bus Scheme (LEBS), announced last year, will provide over £30m to help buy several hundred low emission buses. The winners of LEBS was announced on 25 July, building on the success of the Green Bus Fund, which ran to 2014. Under the Green Bus Fund, £89million of Government funding helped to purchase over 1,200 green buses.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is also encouraging the uptake of greener vehicles through the Bus Service Operators Grant low carbon emission bus incentive.</p><p> </p><p>The Bus Services Bill, which was introduced into the House of Lords on 19<sup>th</sup> May, will provide local transport authorities with new powers to specify the emission standards to be met by local bus services – including through franchising and, with sufficient support from bus operators, under enhanced partnership arrangements.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has also invested over £26million since 2011 under the Clean Bus and Clean Vehicle Technology Funds for local authorities in pollution hotspots across England to retrofit 1000’s of buses, and other vehicles, with pollution reducing technology. This includes converting some buses to either natural gas or to electric propulsion.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-10-13T12:55:19.813Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592881/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592881/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592881/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-03","Bus Services","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the capacity of the bus industry to meet the challenges arising from the need to deal with levels of air pollution in cities.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL2007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592882","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-13","<p>The information is considered commercially sensitive because of the impact it could have on a listed company if released at this time. This information would only be disclosed to franchise bidders on a confidential basis at the time a franchise is re-let. However, under the normal process we would expect bidders to make their own revenue forecasts.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-10-13T12:58:55.657Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592882/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592882/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592882/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-03","Railways: Competition","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon on 20 September (HL1612), why their estimates of the financial impact of the Office of Road and Rail’s decision on the East Coast Main Line and other associated franchises are considered "commercially sensitive" information when they will need to be disclosed to any bidders for future franchises.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL2008"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592883","HM Treasury","false","2016-10-17","<p>Current rules require that cider duty is structured in bands according to the strength of the product.</p><p> </p><p>The government continues to keep all taxes under review, and in that context is considering the views of stakeholders.</p>",,"Lord Young of Cookham",,"2016-10-17T15:50:03.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592883/answer","Biography information for Lord Young of Cookham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592883/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592883/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-10-03","Cider: Excise Duties","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have to change the current duty structure for cider in the light of their statement that alcohol duties should be directly proportional to alcohol content.","false","Biography information for Baroness Finlay of Llandaff",,"Baroness Finlay of Llandaff","HL2009"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592884","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-10-11","<p>​The Governor is Her Majesty's representative on St Helena and is responsible for administering the St Helena Government. The Governor is appointed on the advice of, and reports on all matters to, the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, acting on behalf of Her Majesty, in order to represent the interests of the people of St Helena.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-10-11T16:02:05.173Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592884/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592884/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592884/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-10-03","St Helena: Politics and Government","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government by whom the Governor of St Helena is appointed; to whom she is responsible; and to whom she reports on issues concerning the airport.","false","Biography information for Lord Foulkes of Cumnock",,"Lord Foulkes of Cumnock","HL2010"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592885","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-10-11","<p>The St Helena Government comprises of:</p><p>A Governor appointed by the Foreign Secretary of behalf of the Queen.</p><p>An Executive Council of twelve elected members and three members of St Helena Government who are appointed by the Governor.</p><p>A Legislative Council of five elected members and three senior members of the St Helena Government who are appointed by the Governor.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-10-11T16:02:23.067Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592885/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592885/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592885/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-10-03","St Helena: Politics and Government","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the composition of the government of St Helena, and by whom each member of that government is appointed or elected.","false","Biography information for Lord Foulkes of Cumnock",,"Lord Foulkes of Cumnock","HL2011"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592886","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-10-11","<p>For Financial Year 2016/17 the Government has agreed to provide funding to St Helena Government which makes up 62% of their recurrent budget and 57% of their capital programme.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-10-11T16:02:54.023Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592886/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592886/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592886/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-10-03","St Helena: Public Expenditure","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what percentage of the (1) annual revenue, and (2) annual capital expenditure, of the government of St Helena is provided by them.","false","Biography information for Lord Foulkes of Cumnock",,"Lord Foulkes of Cumnock","HL2012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592887","Department for International Development","false","2016-10-17","<p>DFID are holding a briefing meeting for all interested peers on St Helena airport on 25 October, between 13:00 and 14:00 in Room 10a (House of Lords). Invitations were issued on 5 October.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2016-10-17T16:44:30.297Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592887/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592887/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592887/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-10-03","St Helena: Airports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Anelay of St Johns on 25 July (HL1170), who is responsible for arranging the promised meeting to brief members of the House on the airport at St Helena, and when it is expected to be held.","false","Biography information for Lord Foulkes of Cumnock",,"Lord Foulkes of Cumnock","HL2013"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592888","Department for International Development","false","2016-10-17","<p>As far as we are aware, the St Helena Government has not received any claims for compensation following the identification of wind shear at St Helena Airport.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2016-10-17T16:44:10.213Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592888/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592888/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592888/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-10-03","St Helena: Airports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what compensation claims have been received by the government of St Helena as a result of the delay in opening the airport to commercial traffic, and how those claims are being dealt with.","false","Biography information for Lord Foulkes of Cumnock",,"Lord Foulkes of Cumnock","HL2014"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592889","Home Office","false","2016-10-17","<p>The Common Travel Area (CTA) arrangement pre-dates the EU and leaders in Ireland and the United Kingdom, including the Northern Ireland Executive have been unequivocal - all want to protect this arrangement.</p><p>To date the use of drones has not been considered as a method of monitoring the border between Northern Ireland and Ireland post-Brexit. Indeed regulation in the UK does not permit the use of drones beyond line of sight . Discussions between the Taoiseach and the Prime Minister have underlined their desire to work together to find a creative and innovative solution and to maintain the closest possible relationship following the UK’s exit from the EU.</p><p>We will continue the high level of collaboration with Ireland on the future of the CTA once the UK has left the EU, avoiding the imposition of fixed immigration controls and being clear that there will be no immediate changes to our practices surrounding the CTA.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2016-10-17T16:16:19.903Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592889/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592889/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/592889/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-03","Borders: Northern Ireland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they have ever considered using drones to monitor Northern Ireland’s post-Brexit border with the Republic of Ireland and the European Union; whether they have any plans to do so; and if not, whether they intend explicitly to rule it out.","false","Biography information for Baroness Goudie",,"Baroness Goudie","HL2015"
